<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
	<id>424664</id>
	<title>Scrollbar not functioning in the addon update window</title>
	<description>
		<paragraph id="1">
			<sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9b4) Gecko/2008030714 Firefox/3.0b4
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.9b4) Gecko/2008030714 Firefox/3.0b4</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="2">
			<sentence id="2.1">Upon initial installation, firefox looks for previously installed addons.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.2">If there are addons that are not compatible with the new version, a window is presented that allows the user to view the addons and check for updates.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.3">If the number of addons exceeds the default window size, a scrollbar is available but does not function.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.4">Attempts to scroll through the addon list makes the window flicker, and the list remains static.</sentence>
			<sentence id="2.5">Since this is one of the first thins a user will see when installing firefox, this should be fixed.</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="3">
			<sentence id="3.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
		</paragraph>
		<paragraph id="4">
			<sentence id="4.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.2">1 Install 10 or so addons under firefox 2 (that are not supported by firefox 3)</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.3">2 Install firefox 3</sentence>
			<sentence id="4.4">3 Attempt to use the scrollbar in the addon window</sentence>
		</paragraph>
	</description>
</bug>
